===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|川|頁|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}.
[[w:Shuowen Jiezi|''Shuowen'']] considers it to be an {{Han compound|川|t1=river|頁|t2=head|ls=ic|nocap=1}} - flowing in the river, i.e. following/obeying the river's current. Compare the English phrase {{m|en|go with the flow}}.

===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|bo|འདུལ||to tame; to subdue}} ({{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}).

Possibly related to {{och-l|循|tr=*sə.lu[n]|to follow}}, {{och-l|馴|tr=*sə.lu[n]|docile}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

